title: Google\Cloud\Compute\V1\Commitment
name: Commitment
description:
Represents a regional Commitment resource.

Creating a commitment resource means that you are purchasing a committed use contract with an explicit start and end time. You can create commitments based on vCPUs and memory usage and receive discounted rates. For full details, read Signing Up for Committed Use Discounts. (== resource_for {$api_version}.regionCommitments ==)

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.compute.v1.Commitment

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data.category
params.description: The category of the commitment. Category MACHINE specifies commitments composed of machine resources such as VCPU or MEMORY, listed in resources. Category LICENSE specifies commitments composed of software licenses, listed in licenseResources. Note that only MACHINE commitments should have a Type specified.

params.name: data.creation_timestamp
params.description: [Output Only] Creation timestamp in RFC3339 text format.

params.description: [Output Only] The unique identifier for the resource. This identifier is defined by the server.

params.name: data.kind
params.description: [Output Only] Type of the resource. Always compute#commitment for commitments.

params.name: data.license_resource
params.description: The license specification required as part of a license commitment.

params.name: data.name
params.description: Name of the resource. Provided by the client when the resource is created. The name must be 1-63 characters long, and comply with RFC1035. Specifically, the name must be 1-63 characters long and match the regular expression [a-z]([-a-z0-9]*[a-z0-9])? which means the first character must be a lowercase letter, and all following characters must be a dash, lowercase letter, or digit, except the last character, which cannot be a dash.

params.name: data.plan
params.description: The plan for this commitment, which determines duration and discount rate. The currently supported plans are TWELVE_MONTH (1 year), and THIRTY_SIX_MONTH (3 years).

params.name: data.region
params.description: [Output Only] URL of the region where this commitment may be used.

params.name: data.reservations
params.description: List of reservations in this commitment.

params.name: data.resources
params.description: A list of commitment amounts for particular resources. Note that VCPU and MEMORY resource commitments must occur together.

params.name: data.self_link
params.description: [Output Only] Server-defined URL for the resource.

params.name: data.start_timestamp
params.description: [Output Only] Commitment start time in RFC3339 text format.

params.name: data.status
params.description: [Output Only] Status of the commitment with regards to eventual expiration (each commitment has an end date defined). One of the following values: NOT_YET_ACTIVE, ACTIVE, EXPIRED.

params.name: data.status_message
params.description: [Output Only] An optional, human-readable explanation of the status.
